Time Complexity -

The rate of increase in time with respect to the input size.

Rules to calculate space complexity
1. Always Calculate time complexity in terms of worst case.
2. Avoid the contant values.
3. Avoid lower bound.

Example: Always calculate the time complexity in terms of worst case.

age = ?
if age >= 80:
  print("Super Senior")
elif age >= 60 and < 80:
  print("Senior")
elif age >= 24 and < 60:
  print("Working Professional")
elif age >= 14 and < 24:
  print("Teen")
else:
  print("Baby")

we will calculate the time complexity in terms of worst case because if the program can handle worst case situation 
than it will definately effecient work on best and average case.
For this program the worst case will if the age is 10
than we need to check all the condition of the program this is the worst case.

Space Complexity-
The space complexity of an algorithm is the total space taken by the algorithm with respect
to the input size.
Space complexity means taken auxilary space and input space in the memory.
Auxilary space means the extra space used to solve the problem.
Input size is used to store the input.

Example -

x = 2, y = 5,  z = 7
total = (x+y+z)
print(total)

So input space is x,y,z
and auxilary space is total variable.
